    {
      "question": "The sum of the squares of two consecutive positive integers is $145$. If the integers are $x$ and $x+1$, the quadratic equation representing this condition is $2x^2 + 2x - 144 = 0$. The roots of the simplified equation $x^2 + x - 72 = 0$ are:",
      "answer": "(B)",
      "solution": {
        "steps": [
          "Factorise the quadratic equation $x^2 + x - 72 = 0$.",
          "Look for two numbers that multiply to $-72$ and add to $1$.",
          "The numbers are $9$ and $-8$.",
          "Write $x^2 + 9x - 8x - 72 = 0$.",
          "Factorise to get $(x+9)(x-8) = 0$.",
          "The solutions are $x = -9$ and $x = 8$. Since the integers must be positive, $x = 8$."
        ],
        "derivation": "$x^2 + x - 72 = 0 \\\\ x^2 + 9x - 8x - 72 = 0 \\\\ x(x+9) - 8(x+9) = 0 \\\\ (x+9)(x-8) = 0 \\\\ x = -9, 8$"
      },
      "topic": "Quadratic Equations",
      "subtopic": "factorisation method",
